The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Jan. 5 (PTI): The National Cadet Corps (NCC) will recruit an extra two lakh cadets.          
	We will be adding two lakh more cadets to our existing strength of 13 lakh. This will help us expand our reach in the country and also give opportunity to more young people to join us. This process would be completed in the next five years, NCC director-general R.K. Karwal told reporters on Monday.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court on Monday admitted a petition filed by Pepsico India challenging a Kerala High Court judgment that denied sales tax exemption to the soft drinks major. The apex court has posted the matter for final hearing on March 3. It has asked the state not to take any coercive measure before that.                   
	 Bharuch (Gujarat) (PTI): Three persons were killed on Monday and five injured when a reactor at a chemical factory in the Ankaleshwar industrial area exploded. Police said the reactor at Shivam Alum Chemical Limited burst because of increased pressure.                   
	 Amravati (PTI): Four persons were injured on Monday when the autorickshaw they were travelling in overturned after a panther pounced on it. Police said the driver lost control when the animal jumped on the auto when it was passing by a forest. The injured were taken to hospital.                  
	 Aurangabad (PTI): A Belgian tourist died of malaria on Sunday after battling for life for two weeks. Ven David, 40, had been admitted to a government hospital. He was on ventilator for the last four days. Vens father, Boom David, who had come to India on Saturday, donated his sons body to the hospital.                  
	 Datia (PTI): Three labourers, sitting by the side of a fire, were killed and seven injured on Sunday night after they were run over by a car near Madhya Pradeshs Datia. The driver was also injured.                                                                                                                           
